{"lemma":"غَرْبُ","slug":"غَرْبُ","root":"غ.ر.ب","root_slug":"غ-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31602","n31603","n31607","n31608","n31609","n31610"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go away, depart, withdraw, leave"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set (of the sun, moon, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be a stranger"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be strange, odd, obscure, difficult to understand"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go away, depart, withdraw, leave"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go west, westward"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to banish, exile, expatriate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَرَبَ (ḡaraba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"west, occident"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vehemence, violence, tempestuousness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the disease of an abscess in the canthus of the eye, lachrymal fistula","examples":[{"text":"دوسر: الماهية: حشيشة يشبه ورقها ورق الحنطة لكنه ألين وله ثمرة لها حجابان أو ثلاثة وعليها شبه الشعر وقد يتخذ منه عصارة وتحفظ وهي أفضل من حشيشه.\nالطبع: حار في الأولى يابس في الثانية.\nالأفعال والخواص: فيها تجفيف وتحليل.\nالأورام والبثور: يلين الأورام التي أخذت تصلب ويمنع صلابتها.\nالزينة: من خواصه أنه يذهب بداء الثعلب.\nأعضاء العين: ينفع من الغرب.","english":"Goatgrass: What it is: A grass the leaves of which resemble the leaves of wheat, but it is more flaccid and it has fruits with two or three envelopes and it has a kind of hair and one may extract a juice from it and it is preserved and better than the grass itself.\nIt’s trait: Hot in the first, dry in the third grade.\nEffects and properties: It is drying and dissolving.\nSwellings and pustules: It softens swellings which have become stiff and prevents their stiffening.\nToiletry: It is amongst its properties that it goes well with baldness.\nParts of the eye: It works against lacrimal fistules."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Euphrates poplar (Populus euphratica)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"willow (Salix spp.)","examples":[{"text":"ويغرس في المواضع الرطب الكبيرة والندوة منها النشم والغرب والصفيراء والأيرج والميس والرند ويتوخى أن يكون شجر الأترج في مواضع مستور عن الريح الجوفية والريح الغربية مكشوف للريح القبلية.","english":"One plants on moist, spacious and humid places there elms, willows, planetree maples, citrons, hackberries, and laurels, and it is to be taken care that the citron is covered from northern and western winds and open for southeastern winds."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of غُرَاب (ḡurāb)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From West Semitic *ḡarab-, cognate with Biblical Hebrew עֲרָבָה (ʿărāḇā́), עָרָב (ʿārāḇ, “poplar, willow”), Aramaic עַרְבָּא (ʿarəbā) / ܥܱܪܒ݂ܳܐ (ʿarəḇā), Tigre ዕርብ (ʿərb /⁠ʿərəb⁠/, “a plant with tendrils”), Soqotri ʿarhíeb, with possible further connections to Akkadian 𒌨𒁀𒌅 (ur-ba-tu, “reed, rush”), Akkadian 𒄑𒇡𒁀𒌓 (^(GIŠ)ṣar-ba-tu₂ /⁠ṣarbatu⁠/, “Euphrates Poplar”)."},"ipa":["/ɣa.ra.ba/","/ɣa.ru.ba/","/ɣar.ra.ba/","/ɣarb/","/ɣa.rab/","/ɣurb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31602","headword_ar":"غَرَبَ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, went, went away, passed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He retired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"عَنِ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaba","text_ar":"غَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) aor. and inf. n. as above; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gr~b","text_ar":"غرّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tgr~b","text_ar":"تغرّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, became distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went to a distance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Augorubo Ean~iY","text_ar":"اُغْرُبْ عَنِّى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withdraw, to a distance from me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaba","text_ar":"غَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gr~b","text_ar":"غرّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, became absent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hidden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) The former is said of a wild animal, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He retired from view,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hid himself, in his lurking-place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabati","text_ar":"غَرَبَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosu","text_ar":"الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbN","text_ar":"غُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribN","text_ar":"مَغْرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is anomalous] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugayoribaAnN","text_ar":"مُغَيْرِبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is more extr.], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun set:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaba Aln~ajomu","text_ar":"غَرَبَ النَّجْمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star set."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as an inf. n. of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaba","text_ar":"غَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persevering"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) in an affair. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabati","text_ar":"غَرَبَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayonN","text_ar":"العَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eye was affected with a tumour such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the inner angle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garuba","text_ar":"غَرُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaAbapN","text_ar":"غَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobapN","text_ar":"غُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobN","text_ar":"غُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a man: see 5. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garuba","text_ar":"غَرُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaAbapN","text_ar":"غَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of language, (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was strange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far from being intelligible; difficult to be understood; obscure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * K, TA.) And in like manner, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garubati Alkalimapu","text_ar":"غَرُبَتِ الكَلِمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The word was strange"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unusual"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariba","text_ar":"غَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garibato","text_ar":"غَرِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a ewe or she-goat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, affected with the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning as expl. below."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in another sense."}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S","Msb","A"]},{"entry_id":"n31603","headword_ar":"غرّب","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagoriybN","text_ar":"تَغْرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in two places: and 4, likewise in two places: ―         -b2-  and see also 5. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went into the west:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in this art.:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he directed himself towards the west."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rq","text_ar":"شرق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~ibo $ar~iqo","text_ar":"غَرِّبْ شَرِّقْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou to the west go thou to the east:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go far and wide"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) [See also 4.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused."},{"kind":"text","text":"him, or it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, distant, remote, far off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed, put away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"him, or it; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Agrb","text_ar":"اغرب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gr~b","text_ar":"غرّب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n. as above, (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He banished"},{"kind":"text","text":"a person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, * Msb, TA,) in which a dishonest action had been committed [by him]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He divorced"},{"kind":"text","text":"a wife. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gr~bhu Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"غرّبهُ الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gr~b Ealayohi","text_ar":"غرّب عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune left him distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagoriybN","text_ar":"تَغْرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also, accord. to the K, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing forth white children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus having two contr. meanings: but this is a mistake; the meaning being, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing forth both white and black children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the bringing forth either of the two kinds only is not thus termed, as Saadee Chelebee has pointed out. (MF, TA.)       -A4-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collecting and eating"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hail and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"snow and hear-frost;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAb","text_ar":"غُرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n31607","headword_ar":"غَرْبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaba","text_ar":"غَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., in several senses. ―         -b2-  As a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remoteness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobapN","text_ar":"غَرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~awaY","text_ar":"النَّوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobapu","text_ar":"غَرْبَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in one of my copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobap","text_ar":"غُرْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remoteness, of the place which one purposes to reach in his journey."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, used as an epithet,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawFY garobapN","text_ar":"نَوًى غَرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in one of my copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobapN","text_ar":"غُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote, place which one purposes to reach in his journey."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAru fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَارُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobapN","text_ar":"غَرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, of such a one is distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAhimu garobapN","text_ar":"دَرَاهِمُ غَرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distant money"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not easily attainable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN garobapN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ غَرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A far-seeing eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lagarobu AlEayoni","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَغَرْبُ العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is far-seeing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of a woman you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobapu AlEayoni","text_ar":"غَرْبَةُ العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algarobu","text_ar":"الغَرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almagoribu","text_ar":"المَغْرِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) which latter is also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almagorabu","text_ar":"المَغْرَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":", but more commonly with kesr, (Msb,) or accord. to analogy it should be with fet-h, but usage has given it kesr, as in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oriqu","text_ar":"المَشْرِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The west;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algarobu","text_ar":"الغَرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aroqu","text_ar":"الشَّرْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almagoribu","text_ar":"المَغْرِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oriqu","text_ar":"المَشْرِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] originally signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sunset,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosi","text_ar":"الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribaAnu","text_ar":"مَغْرِبَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and is likewise used to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the time of sunset;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also as an inf. n.: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmagoribaAni","text_ar":"المَغْرِبَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two places"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"points"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the sun sets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the furthest"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"northernmost"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of sunset in summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"[W. 26 degrees N. in Central Arabia]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the furthest"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"southernmost"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of sunset in winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"[W. 26 degrees S. in Central Arabia]: (T, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between these two points are a hundred and eighty points, every one of which is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribN","text_ar":"مَغْرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so between the two points called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oriqaAni","text_ar":"المَشْرِقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) of a thing (K) [and particularly] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the run"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse. (S.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K) of a thing, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbN","text_ar":"غُرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or of a sword and of anything; (S;) and thus [particularly] the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAb","text_ar":"غُرَاب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^os","text_ar":"فَاْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or adz, &c.]. (S, K.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, TA) of a sword, (TA,) or of anything, such as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^os","text_ar":"فَاْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or adz, &c.], and of the knife, (Msb,) and (Msb, TA) (assumed tropical:)  of the tongue: (S, A, Msb, TA:) and [as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness of temper"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, passionateness, irritability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a man, (TA,) and of a horse, (S, TA,) and of youth: (A, TA:) [from the same word signifying the “ edge ” of a sword &c.: whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohifo","text_ar":"اَرْهِفْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garoba *ihonika lamaA A^aquwlu","text_ar":"غَرْبَ ذِهْنِكَ لَمَا اَقُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(mentioned in the A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arhf","text_ar":"ارهف"},{"kind":"text","text":") meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharpen the edge of thine intellect for what I say:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobapN","text_ar":"غَرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence of might"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of valour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awokapN","text_ar":"شَوْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [And hence, app., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Briskness, liveliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightliness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perseverance"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an affair: see the first paragraph.] ―         -b4-  Also, [used as an epithet,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a sword [and the like], and to a tongue. (TA.) And, applied to a horse, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That runs much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that casts himself forward, with uninterrupted running, not desisting until he has gone far with his ride."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalow","text_ar":"دَلْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern bucket"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of a bull's hide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one draws water on the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-camel, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAniyap","text_ar":"سَانِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Msb:) of the masc. gender: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbN","text_ar":"غُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) So expl. in the following words of a trad.:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a","text_ar":"اَخَذَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~alowa Eumaru faA@sotaHaAlato garobFA","text_ar":"الدَّلْوَ عُمَرُ فَا@سْتَحَالَتْ غَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Omar took the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dlw","text_ar":"دلو"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it became changed into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"grb","text_ar":"غرب"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e. when he took the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dlw","text_ar":"دلو"},{"kind":"text","text":"to draw water, it became large in his hand: for the conquests in his time were more than those in the time of Aboo-Bekr. (IAth, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any beast, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAwiyap","text_ar":"رَاوِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which water is carried."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day of irrigation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but [this is app. a mistake: for] Az says that Lth has mentioned the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY yawomi","text_ar":"فِى يَوْمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobK","text_ar":"غَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning thereby"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a day in which water is drawn with the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large bucket called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for irrigation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-camel, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAniyap","text_ar":"سَانِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tears"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they come forth from the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbN","text_ar":"غُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maA laka laA ta*okuru A^um~a Eamoriw\n                      \n                     \n                        A_il~aA liEayonayoka guruwbN tajoriY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What aileth thee, that thou dost not mention Umm-'Amr but thine eyes have tears flowing?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) And it is said of Ibn-'Abbás, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna mivaj~FA yasiylu garobFA","text_ar":"كَانَ مِثَجًّا يَسِيلُ غَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was an eloquent orator, flowing with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a copious and uninterrupted"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2242},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stream of knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ tears coming forth from the eye. ” (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiylN","text_ar":"مَسِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinohilaAlN","text_ar":"اِنْهِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A, K,) in one copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinohimaAlN","text_ar":"اِنْهِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of tears from the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single flow"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoDapN","text_ar":"فَيْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of tears, and of wine. (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"duct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the channel of the tears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that flows"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with tears"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterruptedly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsuwrN","text_ar":"نَاسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh.) One says of a person whose tears flow without intermission,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEayonihi garobN","text_ar":"بَعَيْنِهِ غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, S, Mgh.) And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alguruwbu","text_ar":"الغُرُوبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The channels of the tears."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b4-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner angle of the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outer angle thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tumour in the inner angles of the eyes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pustule"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bavorapN","text_ar":"بَثْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which discharges blood, and the bleeding of which will not be stopped."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abundance of saliva"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moisture thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of saliva:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbN","text_ar":"غُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where the saliva collects and remains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a tooth is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where the saliva"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collects and remains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbN","text_ar":"غُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='","text_ar":"مَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lustre"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, TA,) of the tooth, (TA,) or of the teeth: (S, TA:) accord. to the T and M and Nh and L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbu AlA^asonaAni","text_ar":"غُرُوبُ الاَسْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the places where the saliva of the teeth collects and remains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their extremities and sharpness and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='","text_ar":"مَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may here mean either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lustre"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='","text_ar":"مَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs upon the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='","text_ar":"مَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and shining whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their fineness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thinness, and sharpness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwbN","text_ar":"غُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serrated, edges"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the fore teeth: it is also, as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. as signifying the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='","text_ar":"مَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fam","text_ar":"فَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by which may be meant either the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water of the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lustre of the teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfamu","text_ar":"الفَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies “ the mouth ” and metonymically “ the teeth ”], and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness of the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and accord. to MF, as on the authority of the Nh, [but SM expresses a doubt as to its correctness,] it is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[themselves]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$anabN","text_ar":"شَنَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.]       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbahu sahomu garobK","text_ar":"اَصَابَهُ سَهْمُ غَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomu garabK","text_ar":"سَهْمُ غَرَبٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomN garobN","text_ar":"سَهْمٌ غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomN garabN","text_ar":"سَهْمٌ غَرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, * K,) the second of which, i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomu garabK","text_ar":"سَهْمُ غَرَبٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to IKt, is the most approved, (MF,) mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow of which the shooter was not known"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb, K:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"shm garob","text_ar":"سهم غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an arrow from an unknown quarter;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"shm","text_ar":"سهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garab","text_ar":"غَرَب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an arrow that is shot and that strikes another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree of El-Hijáz,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick, and thorny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence is made"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuHayol","text_ar":"كُحَيْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mangy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels are smeared:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or it is a coll. gen. n., for] its n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says ISd:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kHyl","text_ar":"كحيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiraAn","text_ar":"قَطِرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the dial. of El-Hijáz: and he [app. ISd] says also, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abohal","text_ar":"اَبْهَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] is the same as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTrAn","text_ar":"قطران"},{"kind":"text","text":"is extracted from it. (TA.) Hence, as some say, (K, TA,) the trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yazaAlu A^aholu Algarobi ZaAhiriyna EalaY","text_ar":"لَا يَزَالُ اَهْلُ الغَرْبِ ظَاهِرِينَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~i","text_ar":"الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"grb","text_ar":"غرب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not cease to be attainers of the truth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the true religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of Syria,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because Syria is [a little to the] west of El-Hijáz: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of sharpness, and of vehemence of might"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of valour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the warriors against unbelievers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of the bucket called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of the west;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which meaning is considered by Iyád and others the most probable, because, in the relation of the trad. by Ed-Dárakutnee, the word in question is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almagorib","text_ar":"المَغْرِب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA","T","A","Mgh","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n31608","headword_ar":"غُرْبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobapN","text_ar":"غُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31609","headword_ar":"غَرَبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Silver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vessel such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAm","text_ar":"جَام"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking-cup"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bowl such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaH","text_ar":"قَدَح"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fadaEodaEaA sur~apa Alr~akaA='i kamaA\n                      \n                     \n                        daEodaEa saAqiY AlA^aEaAjimi AlgarabaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"cited in the S as being by El-Aashà but it is said in the L, IB says, this verse is by Lebeed, not by El-Aashà, describing two torrents meeting together; meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they filled the middle of the valley of Er-Rehà,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, but less correctly, called Er-Rikà,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like as the cup-bearer of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEAjm","text_ar":"اعاجم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigners"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fills the silver"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaH","text_ar":"قَدَح"},{"kind":"text","text":"with wine: the verse of El-Aashà in which [it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garab","text_ar":"غَرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs as meaning “ silver ” is,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA A@nokab~a A^azoharu bayona Als~uqaApi\n                      \n                     \n                        taraAmawoA bihi garabFA wanuDaAraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When a white wine-jug is turned down so as to pour out its contents"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the cup-bearers"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they hand it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the wine in the cups,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one to another"},{"kind":"text","text":"[while it resembles"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver or gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (L, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabFA","text_ar":"غَرَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here in the accus. case as a denotative of state, though signifying a substance: [and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuDaAraA","text_ar":"نُضَارَا"},{"kind":"text","text":":] but it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuDaArN","text_ar":"نُضَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify species of trees from which are made [drinkingcups or bowls such as are termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqodaAH","text_ar":"اَقْدَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaHN","text_ar":"قَدَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and it is said in the T that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuDaArN","text_ar":"نُضَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a species of trees from which are made yellow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqodaAH","text_ar":"اَقْدَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [In explanation of the last of the applications of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned above, it is said that] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, ISd, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from which are made white"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking-cups"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bowls of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqodaAH","text_ar":"اَقْدَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isbiydo daAr","text_ar":"اـِسبِيدْ دَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isoPiydaAr","text_ar":"اـِسْپِيدَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) [generally held to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the Hebr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"עֲרָבִים","text_ar":"עֲרָבִים","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or particularly the species called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salix Babylonica:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd, TA.) [Avicenna (Ibn-Seenà), in book ii. p. 279, mentions a tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"grb","text_ar":"غرب"},{"kind":"text","text":", but describes only the uses and supposed properties of its bark &c., particularizing its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Samog","text_ar":"صَمْغ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whence it appears that he means the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", not the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garab","text_ar":"غَرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vessel of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaH","text_ar":"قَدَح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps such as is made from the species of trees above mentioned]: (K, TA:) and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agoraAbN","text_ar":"اَغْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b6-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water that drops from the buckets between the well and the watering-trough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which soon alters in odour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any water that pours from the buckets from about the mouth of the well to the wateringtrough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank, and that soon alters in odour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water and mud that are around the well and the watering-trough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and (as some say, TA) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odour of water and mud:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so called because it soon alters. (TA.) [Hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tgrb","text_ar":"لا تغرب"},{"kind":"text","text":", [thus in the TA, so that it may be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tagorubo","text_ar":"لا تَغْرُبْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tugar~ibo","text_ar":"لا تُغَرِّبْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tugoribo","text_ar":"لا تُغْرِبْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spill not thou the water between the well and the watering-trough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank, so as to make mud."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaf","text_ar":"سَعَف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the she-camel, in consequence of which the hair of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuroTuwm","text_ar":"خُرْطُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the nose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that of the eyes fall off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  And ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A colour such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaraq","text_ar":"زَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the eye of a horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together with whiteness thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half, in five places."}],"source_refs":["L","TA","T","S","ISd","K"]},{"entry_id":"n31610","headword_ar":"غُرُبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybN","text_ar":"غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}